sample_data.Bio:
Josh Burnette graduated from Mississippi State University in 2012 with a Bachelor of Science in Civil Engineering. Since then, Mr. Burnette has developed extensive experience across a wide range of engineering and construction projects in Tennessee, Mississippi, and Texas. His expertise includes sanitary sewer systems, domestic water systems, grading and drainage, stormwater an detention, erosion control, land development, and state and federal permitting. 

While his primary experience is in engineering, his time working as a contractor provided valuable insight into how design decisions impact project schedules and budgets. This hands-on experience, constructing projects from other professionals' plans, refined his approach to creating detailed, clear plans that effectively communicate design intent and facilitate smoother, more efficient construction. 

Currently, Mr. Burnette oversees the RDS engineering and planning team while managing a range of sub-consultants including surveying, landscaping, site lighting, architecture, and environmental services to ensure timely application submittals. He also coordinates with surveyors and contractors to keep development projects on schedule and within budget
